quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,Truly the reverent shall have a place of triumph
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,buxom maidens of like age
  78,34,and an overflowing cup
  78,35,They hear therein neither idle talk nor lying—
  78,36,"a recompense from thy Lord, a gift abounding—"
  78,37,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and whatsoever is between them, the Compassionate, Whom they have no power to address"
  78,38,"That Day the Spirit and the angels stand in rows, none speaking, save one whom the Compassionate permits and who speaks aright"
  78,39,"That is the True Day. So let whosoever will, take a path of return unto his Lord"
  78,40,"Truly We have warned you of a punishment nigh, on a day when a man beholds what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever says, “Oh, would that I were dust!”"